        "city_summary": "Lawrence is a city in and the county seat of Douglas County, Kansas, United States, It is in the northeastern sector of the state, astride Interstate 70, between the Kansas and Wakarusa rivers. As of the 2020 census, the population of the city was 94,934, making it the sixth-largest city in the state. The city is a college town with a significant student population, because it is home to both the University of Kansas (KU) and Haskell Indian Nations University (HINU).",
